### V0.12 — Public DNS Delegation

Verify the subdomain delegation is configured correctly at the registrar:

```bash
# Nameserver A records — should return your public IP
dig A dns1.{{ domain }}
# Expected: {{ public_ip }}

dig A dns2.{{ domain }}
# Expected: {{ public_ip }}

# Subdomain delegation — should return your DNS servers
dig NS prod.{{ domain }}
# Expected: dns1.{{ domain }}. and dns2.{{ domain }}.

# Base domain NS — should still be the registrar's nameservers
dig NS {{ domain }}
# Expected: IONOS default nameservers (NOT dns1/dns2.{{ domain }})
```

- [ ] `dig A dns1.{{ domain }}` returns `{{ public_ip }}`
- [ ] `dig A dns2.{{ domain }}` returns `{{ public_ip }}`
- [ ] `dig NS prod.{{ domain }}` returns `dns1.{{ domain }}` and `dns2.{{ domain }}`
- [ ] `dig NS {{ domain }}` still returns the registrar's default nameservers (unchanged)
- [ ] Dev DNS is NOT publicly delegated (no NS records for dev.{{ domain }})

